{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881682825,"sessionID":"ses_2853474a4ffeJw71Wrl49XNHYW","part":{"id":"prt_d7acbf127001hVARpX6GWtL0u5","messageID":"msg_d7acbda15001JQC6XnzDx3r3fd","sessionID":"ses_2853474a4ffeJw71Wrl49XNHYW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-018\n6: **Module:** `pkg/agentd`\n7: **Language:** Go\n8: **Size:** S\n9: **Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md)\n10: \n11: The Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). It uses the controller-runtime framework for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Reconciliation Trigger\n18: \n19: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager's API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n22: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n23: - **AND** the agentd manager is running\n24: - **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the change\n25: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked with the object's namespace and name\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Sandbox deletion triggers reconcile\n28: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is deleted from the cluster\n29: - **AND** the agentd manager is running\n30: - **WHEN** the controller-runtime detects the deletion\n31: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function SHALL be invoked to handle cleanup\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### Requirement: Idle Detection Input\n36: \n37: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue.\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n40: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists without the `last-activity-time` annotation\n41: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n42: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n43: - **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Empty annotation value means no deletion\n46: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` exists with `last-activity-time` annotation set to empty string\n47: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n48: - **THEN** the sandbox SHALL NOT be deleted\n49: - **AND** the result SHALL have zero `RequeueAfter`\n50: \n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 316. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018: Agentd 空闲清理控制器 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018\n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n**Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). It uses the controller-runtime framework for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation Trigger\n\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager's API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775881682798,"end":1775881682822}}}}
