{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881689464,"sessionID":"ses_2853474a4ffeJw71Wrl49XNHYW","part":{"id":"prt_d7acc106c001Eu5YbxrV82GvYW","messageID":"msg_d7acbffb80012M30VOu62YED7I","sessionID":"ses_2853474a4ffeJw71Wrl49XNHYW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775881689453,"end":1775881689462}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881689476,"sessionID":"ses_2853474a4ffeJw71Wrl49XNHYW","part":{"id":"prt_d7acc14500017Wjf1NGmsHOnK6","messageID":"msg_d7acbffb80012M30VOu62YED7I","sessionID":"ses_2853474a4ffeJw71Wrl49XNHYW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","limit":40},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 (Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller)\n2: \n3: > **Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n4: > **Language:** Go  \n5: > **Size:** S  \n6: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n7: > **Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md), idle-cleanup/design.md\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: AR-018 implements the Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller that watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). The controller uses controller-runtime for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-4.1 — Package Structure and Constants\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 4.1.1 | Create `pkg/agentd/` directory structure | Directory exists | 0.25h |\n22: | 4.1.2 | Create `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | File compiles | 0.5h |\n23: | 4.1.3 | Define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute` constant | Constant defined and exported | 0.25h |\n24: | 4.1.4 | Define `RequeueAfterParseError = 30 * time.Second` constant | Constant defined and exported | 0.25h |\n25: | 4.1.5 | Add package-level doc comment | `go doc ./pkg/agentd` shows overview | 0.25h |\n26: \n27: **Deliverable:** Package structure compiles with constants defined.\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## ST-4.2 — Reconciler Struct and Interface\n32: \n33: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n34: |---|------|--------------|------|\n35: | 4.2.1 | Define `Reconciler` struct with `client.Client` and `Scheme *runtime.Scheme` fields | Struct matches delta-spec | 0.5h |\n36: | 4.2.2 | Import required packages (`sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client`, `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime`) | All imports resolve | 0.25h |\n37: | 4.2.3 | Import `workloadmanager` package for annotation key constant | Import path correct | 0.25h |\n38: | 4.2.4 | Import Sandbox types from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Type references compile | 0.5h |\n39: \n40: **Deliverable:** Reconciler struct defined with correct fields and imports.\n\n(Showing lines 1-40 of 284. Use offset=41 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器 (Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** S  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** client-go library (deployment/client-go.md), idle-cleanup/design.md\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-018 implements the Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller that watches `Sandbox` custom resources and deletes them when they have been inactive beyond a configured grace period (15 minutes). The controller uses controller-runtime for reconciliation and reads the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine idle status.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Package Structure and Constants\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-018/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775881689456,"end":1775881689474}}}}
