ube-ref/cmd/cli/`.\n  Line 11: | `agentcube/cli/__init__.py` | CLI subpackage marker |\n  Line 52:     \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n  Line 371: ## Dependencies (`cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/deployment/spec.md:\n  Line 77: ### Requirement: Docker images for core binaries\n  Line 83: - **THEN** the image SHALL compile the respective Go binary with `CGO_ENABLED=0` and run it from Alpine 3.19 as a non-root user (`apiserver` UID 1000 or `router` UID 1000) exposing port 8080\n  Line 86: The system SHALL expose Make targets to build binaries (`build`, related targets), run tests (`test`), build/push Docker images (`docker-*`), run code generation (`generate`, `gen-crd`, `gen-client`, `gen-all`, `gen-check`), and run E2E (`e2e`, `e2e-clean`).\n  Line 91: - **THEN** `bin/workloadmanager` SHALL be produced from `./cmd/workload-manager` after `generate`\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-routing/design.md:\n  Line 24: ### CLI flags (`cmd/router/main.go`)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md:\n  Line 1: # AgentCube CLI (cli-toolkit) Specification\n  Line 9: ### Requirement: Global CLI options\n  Line 13: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n  Line 15: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n  Line 23: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n  Line 28: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n  Line 33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n  Line 38: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n  Line 51: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n  Line 85: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n  Line 90: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n  Line 107: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n  Line 179: ### Requirement: AgentCube provider integration (CLI)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/code-execution/design.md:\n  Line 3: Derived from `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` and `cmd/picod` in `/tmp/agentcube-ref`. Field names, types, tags, and constants match the Go definitions.\n  Line 7: - **Main**: `cmd/picod/main.go` — parses flags, constructs `picod.Config`, `picod.NewServer(config)`, `server.Run()`.\n  Line 9: ## CLI flags and defaults\n  Line 85: - **Stdout/Stderr**: `bytes.Buffer` assigned to `cmd.Stdout` and `cmd.Stderr`; no `cmd.Stdin` assignment.\n  Line 86: - **Exit code**: If `errors.Is(ctx.Err(), context.DeadlineExceeded)` → `TimeoutExitCode`; else if `cmd.ProcessState != nil` → `ExitCode()`; else `1` and append `err.Error()` to stderr (with newline if stderr non-empty).\n  Line 241: - `Content-Transfer-Encoding`: `binary`\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/code-execution/spec.md:\n  Line 47: - **THEN** `cmd.Dir` is set to the sanitized absolute path; if resolution fails, the server responds HTTP 400 with `error` prefixed by `\"Invalid working directory: \"`\n  Line 53: - **THEN** `cmd.Env` is the current process environment plus additional entries `key=value` for each map entry\n  Line 119: - **THEN** the server sets `Content-Description` to `File Transfer`, `Content-Transfer-Encoding` to `binary`, `Content-Disposition` to `attachment; filename=\"<basename>\"`, `Content-Type` from `mime.TypeByExtension` or `application/octet-stream`, and returns the file body\n  Line 173: The system SHALL read CLI flags `-port` and `-workspace`, build `picod.Config`, and listen on `\":<port>\"`. If `workspace` is empty, the workspace root SHALL be the current working directory (fatal if `os.Getwd` fails). The HTTP server SHALL use `ReadHeaderTimeout` of 10 seconds.\n  Line 175: #### Scenario: Defaults from CLI\n  Line 178: - **WHEN** the binary starts\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md:\n  Line 17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 104 matches (4 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":104,"truncated":true},"title":"binary|binaries|CLI|cmd","time":{"start":1775881701914,"end":1775881701922}}}}
